  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Workplace Safety and Health Officer",
  "description": "<p><em>Jobs Description:</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Advise the occupier, Project Manager, or any person in charge of the Site on measures necessary to ensure the safety and health of all persons employed on-site.</li>\n  <li>Implement safety measures with the approval of the occupier, General Manager, or relevant authority.</li>\n  <li>Conduct personal inspections of the Site to identify any machinery, plant, equipment, appliance, or manual labor practices that may pose a risk of bodily harm to any worker.</li>\n  <li>Discuss inspection findings with the occupier, Factory Manager, Project Manager, and Safety Supervisor responsible for the relevant equipment or operations.</li>\n  <li>Investigate accidents or occupational diseases that occur on-site and recommend corrective actions to prevent recurrence.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and verify the implementation of all recommended corrective actions.</li>\n  <li>Organize safety-related activities such as trainings, talks, competitions, or campaigns to promote and sustain safety awareness among workers.</li>\n  <li>Serve as the Secretary of the Site Safety Committee, supporting the Committee Chairman in executing the committee’s responsibilities.</li>\n  <li>Preside over meetings of the Site Safety Committee in the absence of the Chairman.</li>\n  <li>Maintain up-to-date safety records relevant to the site’s operations.</li>\n  <li>Fulfill all duties as required under the Workplace Safety and Health Act and other applicable regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>MOM Singapore Registered Workplace Safety &amp; Health Officer</li>\n  <li>⁠WSQ Specialist Diploma in Workplace Safety and Health (Level C) </li>\n  <li>⁠WSQ Advanced Certificate in Workplace Safety and Health (Level B)</li>\n  <li>Preferred Candidate that Posses Own Transport</li>\n</ul>",
